---
import Layout from "../components/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout title="Home">
  <section class="flex flex-col gap-10">
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 sm:items-center">
      <!-- Photo placeholder (we’ll replace with your real image) -->
      <img
        src="/me.jpg"
        alt="Photo of Alex Doyoon Kim"
        width="176"
        height="176"
        class="h-44 w-44 rounded-full object-cover object-top border border-zinc-200 shrink-0"
      />


      <div class="flex-1">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold">Alex Doyoon Kim</h1>
        <p class="mt-2 text-zinc-700">
          Recent CS graduate with a programming languages research background (OCaml, type systems, proof assistants)
          and experience building full-stack applications. Currently shipping a set of deployed portfolio projects in web + cloud.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-3 text-sm">
          <a class="rounded-lg border px-3 py-2 hover:bg-zinc-50" href="/resume">Resume</a>
          <a class="rounded-lg border px-3 py-2 hover:bg-zinc-50" href="/projects">Projects</a>
          <a class="rounded-lg border px-3 py-2 hover:bg-zinc-50" href="https://github.com/alexkim715" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
		  <a class="rounded-lg border px-3 py-2 hover:bg-zinc-50" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alex-dyk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
		  <a class="rounded-lg border px-3 py-2 hover:bg-zinc-50" href="mailto:alex.dy.kim7@gmail.com">Email</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="grid gap-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Highlights</h2>
      <ul class="grid gap-3 text-zinc-800">
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium">Programming Languages Research:</span>
          Built and extended type inference infrastructure for a research language (Pirouette), implementing unification-based inference in OCaml.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium">Teaching (TA):</span>
          Supported large courses in Data Structures and Programming Languages (300–350+ students/semester) through recitations, office hours, and grading support.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium">Portfolio Build (in progress):</span>
          Shipping three industry-focused projects: a deployed CRUD app (auth + Postgres), an AWS deployment project (CI/CD + basic observability), and a PL-focused web tool.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="grid gap-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Featured (planned)</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-3">
        <div class="rounded-xl border p-4">
          <div class="font-medium">B1 — Full-stack CRUD app (in progress)</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-zinc-700 mt-1">Auth + Postgres + deployed. Focus: schema/migrations, ownership rules, clean UX.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border p-4">
          <div class="font-medium">B2 — AWS deployment project (planned)</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-zinc-700 mt-1">CI/CD + logs + health checks. Focus: operating what I build.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border p-4">
          <div class="font-medium">B3 — PL tool with a web UI (planned)</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-zinc-700 mt-1">A small developer tool to visualize/inspect program structure (AST/types/steps).</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>
</Layout>
